!! Using the Console

The Console is JSON Convert's day-to-day workflow surface.  This guide walks every step: loading source, picking a profile, converting, reviewing the staging area, applying, and tracking what landed.

If you haven't read the [[Profile Guide]] yet, you can still follow along here -- the Console mechanics don't depend on understanding profile internals.  When you want to know //why// a binding produced what it did, that's the Profile Guide's territory.

